# ruvector-mmwave-bridge — environment template.
#
# Drop edited copy at /etc/ruvector-mmwave-bridge.env and the systemd
# unit will source it. Comment characters and quote rules are
# systemd EnvironmentFile= conventions, not bash.
#
# All variables are referenced from
# /etc/systemd/system/ruvector-mmwave-bridge.service.

# ---- Required ----

# Serial device the radar enumerates as. Typical values:
#   Seeed MR60BHA2 USB stick (CP2102 bridge):   /dev/ttyUSB0
#   Custom MR60 board with native USB-CDC:      /dev/ttyACM0
# install-mmwave-bridge.sh sets up a udev rule giving the ruvector-bridge
# group rw on these nodes regardless of which one the kernel picks.
RUVECTOR_BRIDGE_DEVICE=/dev/ttyUSB0

# Cluster sink — comma-separated host:port list of the hailo-backend
# workers' gRPC endpoints. Same flag as embed/bench --workers.
RUVECTOR_BRIDGE_WORKERS=100.77.59.83:50051,100.77.59.84:50051

# sha256 hex of the cluster's HEF + vocab artifacts. Required by the
# ADR-172 §2a gate when the bridge operates with a non-zero cache;
# unset means "no enforcement", which the gate will refuse unless
# RUVECTOR_BRIDGE_EXTRA_ARGS includes --allow-empty-fingerprint.
RUVECTOR_BRIDGE_FINGERPRINT=

# ---- Optional ----

# Extra args appended verbatim to the ExecStart command. Useful for:
#   --baud 115200            (non-stock radar baud)
#   --dim 384                (non-MiniLM cluster dim)
#   --quiet                  (suppress informational stderr)
#   --allow-empty-fingerprint (legacy fleet without an HEF)
#   --auto                   (override --device with auto-scan)
#
# Iter 242/243/245 cluster-side knobs (recommended for prod deploys):
#   --cache 4096             coordinator-side LRU; ~32500x speedup at
#                            full hit rate. Radar NL templates have
#                            small-cardinality fields so steady-state
#                            telemetry fills the cache after warmup.
#   --cache-ttl 300          5-minute max-staleness on cached entries;
#                            bounds drift after a silent worker reconfig.
#   --health-check 30        every 30s probe each worker, eject on
#                            fingerprint mismatch, clear cache on event.
#                            Closes the long-running bridge silent-drift
#                            window described in iter-245's commit.
#
# All three play nicely together; the typical hardened deploy is:
#   RUVECTOR_BRIDGE_EXTRA_ARGS=--cache 4096 --cache-ttl 300 --health-check 30
RUVECTOR_BRIDGE_EXTRA_ARGS=

# ---- TLS / mTLS (iter 120, requires `--features tls` build) ----
#
# Default plaintext gRPC + Tailscale's WireGuard envelope is fine for
# many deploys. For LAN deploys or any cluster running with §1b mTLS,
# enable TLS via these flags. They get appended to ExecStart through
# the EXTRA_ARGS mechanism above; e.g.:
#
#   RUVECTOR_BRIDGE_EXTRA_ARGS=--tls-ca /etc/ruvector-bridge/ca.pem \
#                              --tls-client-cert /etc/ruvector-bridge/client.pem \
#                              --tls-client-key  /etc/ruvector-bridge/client.key
#
# --tls-ca         server CA bundle (PEM). Required to enable TLS.
# --tls-domain     SNI to assert (default = hostname of first --workers).
# --tls-client-cert + --tls-client-key  enable §1b mTLS (must both be set).
